The program is correct and will produce the expected result "B". The bug wa
was that even though loop iteration was happening over all events, `lastApp
`lastApproved` variable was not updated when `approved` for an event was fa
false. 

Here's the corrected code:

```tundra
val events = [
   { id: "A", approved: true },
   { id: "B", approved: true },
   { id: "C", approved: false }
];

var lastApproved = "none";
for(event in events) {
  if (event.approved){
    lastApproved = event.id;
  }
}
print(lastApproved);
```
This code will now update `lastApproved` to the id of the most recent appro
approved event, even when a non-approved event occurs later in the list. Th
The final value of `lastApproved` would be "B", as it's the last event with
with `approved: true` and before an event with `approved: false` occurs.
